edia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9714392081891466, \"rank\": 0.0256772378001994, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 776, \"end\": 782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965774217846711, \"rank\": 0.0028647772138614405, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A non-French employer\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Secondment is a temporary assignment of an employee from a company established in a non-French country to work in France.\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9714392081891466, \"rank\": 0.0256772378001994, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Secondment\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"a temporary assignment\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 844}, {\"ngram\": \"an employee\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"a company\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"a non-French country\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 910}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under this temporary assignment, the employee remains employed by the non-French company.\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 1020, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this temporary assignment\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"the employee\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"the non-French company\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Secondment is applicable in different situations and can either involve a French company (customer or end user) or not.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1096, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965774217846711, \"rank\": 0.0028647772138614405, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Secondment\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1032}, {\"ngram\": \"different situations\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1070}, {\"ngram\": \"customer\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1120}, {\"ngram\": \"end user\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, there is no need for the non-French employer to set up a specific relationship with a French company in order to validly second its employees in France.\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965774217846711, \"rank\": 0.0028647772138614405, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9714392081891466, \"rank\": 0.0256772378001994, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1156}, {\"ngram\": \"no need\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"the non-French employer\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"a specific relationship\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1267}, {\"ngram\": \"its employees\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Depending on the situation, the non-French employer will have to comply with key formalities before having its seconded employees in France.1 In most situations, non-French employers will have to: The above is only required for employees, i.e., individuals who are subject to employment law (excluding independent contractors or freelancers who are not considered as employees).\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"the non-French employer\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"key formalities\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"its seconded employees\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1441}, {\"ngram\": \"France.1\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"most situations\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"non-French employers\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"i.e., individuals\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1568}, {\"ngram\": \"employment law\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"independent contractors\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"freelancers\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Non-French employers should check whether the employees to be seconded in France need a visa or a work permit and should apply in advance to get the relevant documentation before starting the secondment in France.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1768, \"end\": 1774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9714392081891466, \"rank\": 0.0256772378001994, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9714392081891466, \"rank\": 0.0256772378001994, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Non-French employers\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1714}, {\"ngram\": \"the employees\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"a visa\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"a work permit\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1803}, {\"ngram\": \"advance\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1831}, {\"ngram\": \"the relevant documentation\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1865}, {\"ngram\": \"the secondment\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1896}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In principle (except specific cases)2: Non-French companies seconding employees in France remain the employer of these employees.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 2039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 1999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9714392081891466, \"rank\": 0.0256772378001994, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"principle\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"specific cases)2\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"Non-French companies\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"the employer\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2018}, {\"ngram\": \"these employees\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seconded employees will, in principle, remain subject to the social security system and social security contributions of their country of origin.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2185, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Seconded employees\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"principle\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"the social security system\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2123}, {\"ngram\": \"social security contributions\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2157}, {\"ngram\": \"their country\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2174}, {\"ngram\": \"origin\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the French public policy principles (i.e., a set of specific fundamental rules mentioned by the French labor code) will apply to seconded employees working in France during the Olympic Games,3including rules relating to working time, public holidays, paid annual leave, and remuneration.4 Non-French employers should pay specific attention to working time requirements as French law has strict and complex requirements in relation to this, meaning that employers may need to adapt their usual working arrangements to ensure that employees meet these requirements.\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2200, \"end\": 2206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965774217846711, \"rank\": 0.0028647772138614405, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2292, \"end\": 2298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965774217846711, \"rank\": 0.0028647772138614405, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2355, \"end\": 2361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9714392081891466, \"rank\": 0.0256772378001994, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9999196879081251, \"rank\": 8.03185198272847e-05, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a set\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2244}, {\"ngram\": \"specific fundamental rules\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"seconded employees\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2343}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games,3including rules\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"working time\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"public holidays\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"annual leave\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"Non-French employers\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2505}, {\"ngram\": \"specific attention\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2535}, {\"ngram\": \"working time requirements\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"strict and complex requirements\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2614}, {\"ngram\": \"relation\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2626}, {\"ngram\": \"employers\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2658}, {\"ngram\": \"their usual working arrangements\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2734}, {\"ngram\": \"these requirements\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, the French labor code provides with several limits on working time: However, the usual daily 10-hour working limit5or the weekly maximum 48-hour limit5may not be sufficient for specific activities.\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2774, \"end\": 2780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965774217846711, \"rank\": 0.0028647772138614405, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several limits\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"working time\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2836}, {\"ngram\": \"the usual daily 10-hour working limit5or\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2887}, {\"ngram\": \"specific activities\", \"from\": 2947, \"to\": 2966}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alternative solutions should be considered.\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alternative solutions\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 2990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some companies may also need to be exempted from the daily rest limit (11 hours)5and may therefore have to apply for such exemption before the French labor inspection.\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3156, \"end\": 3162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965774217846711, \"rank\": 0.0028647772138614405, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some companies\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3027}, {\"ngram\": \"the daily rest limit\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3082}, {\"ngram\": \"such exemption\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A decree dated23 November 20236provides for an exemption to weekly rest requirements (that is usually granted on Sundays) for the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3326, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A decree dated23\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3198}, {\"ngram\": \"November 20236provides\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3221}, {\"ngram\": \"an exemption\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3238}, {\"ngram\": \"weekly rest requirements\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3266}, {\"ngram\": \"Sundays\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3302}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This exemption applies for the strict period from 18 July 2024 to 14 August 2024 and under specific conditions (i.e., very specific activities).\", \"from\": 3327, \"to\": 3471, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This exemption\", \"from\": 3327, \"to\": 3341}, {\"ngram\": \"the strict period\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 337